OL,7,FFour-year-old Noah was once an active
OL,8,Fchild who loved to play with his
OL,9,Ffriends. But recently, sat on a park
OL,10,Fbench with his mother, he said "nobody
OL,11,Flikes me or wants to play with me".
OL,13,FThe youngster has been so poorly for
OL,14,Fjust over a third of his short life
OL,15,Fwith long Covid. He is one many
OL,16,Fthousands of children struggling with
OL,17,Flingering symptoms such as fatigue,
OL,18,Fjoint pain, respiratory issues, skin
OL,19,Frashes and heart palpitations for
OL,20,Fmonths or beyond after infection.
OL,3,C'My four-year-old walks like he is
OL,4,Cdrunk': The devastating impact of long
OL,5,CCovid on children
